Pre-Game Insights: Guinea-Bissau and Egypt are undefeated in World Cup qualifying heading into Monday's fourth encounter in Group A at Estadio Nacional 24 de Setembro.
Guinea-Bissau have played out two draws, seeing them already adrift of the unblemished North African side.
Egypt claimed maximum points in a potential banana skin to defeat Burkina Faso 2-1 last time out, sealing success for the African giants in pole position to advance automatically from Group A.
